headline: CNN Live Event/Special
subHeadline: New Year's Eve Live with Anderson Cooper and Andy Cohen. Aired 8-9p ET

utterances.speaker: JOE JONAS, AMERICAN SINGER
utterances.sentences: Hey, we're The Jonas Brothers.

utterances.speaker: KEVIN JONAS, AMERICAN SINGER
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year, Andy and Anderson. We are so excited to be performing for you tonight.

utterances.speaker: NICK JONAS, AMERICAN SINGER
utterances.sentences: We can't wait to see our fans all across the world next year on tour. Happy 2024.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.sentences: From the heart of Times Square, it's CNN's New Year's Eve Live. Welcome to TV's Wildest Party, with performances by Maroon 5, Enrique Iglesias, The Jonas Brothers, Miranda Lambert, Darius Rucker, Flo Rida, and Rod Stewart. With special appearances by John Mayer, Patti Labelle, Jeremy Renner, Amy Sedaris, Neil Patrick Harris, Bowen Yang and Matt Rogers, David Blaine, Bridget Everett, Eva Longoria, and more surprises.And now, your hosts, Anderson Cooper and Andy Cohen.

utterances.speaker: ANDERSON COOPER, CNN HOST
utterances.sentences: And good evening. Welcome to Times Square, New York City. The city that never sleeps. It feels like it's at the end of a year-long bender tonight. There are protests in parts of the city. Times Square, though, is as locked down as I've ever seen it. Hundreds of thousands of people.I think they're expecting as many as a million, and I'm joined by my partner in crime, Andy Cohen.

utterances.speaker: ANDY COHEN, AMERICAN TV PRESENTER
utterances.sentences: Hey, Anderson.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year. Isn't not exciting?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It's freezing cold.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It's not. I think it's deceptive. Everyone keeps saying it's balmy, but we're also very protective.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: This was our -- this is our seventh year doing this together.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: This is our seventh year.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It's like my 20th year in Times Square. And we've had some incredibly cold nights, but it's like just about 40 degrees here.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And I'm hoping it stays that way.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It's going to be a lot of fun.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Four and a half hours.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Four and a half hours.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You've often said this is like a telethon with no disease.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I've been known to mention that a little bit.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, you have. I stole that line from you at one point.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, you did.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: That's why I bring it up.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We've got a lot of fun guests. Henry Winkler, who I've been obsessed with since I was a little kid.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Me too. He's joining us from Hawaii.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I know. Jeremy Renner.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Jeremy Renner is going to be here. John Mayer is joining us from Tokyo, Japan.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Have you ever heard of Tokyo, Japan?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I have. I have.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, Andy. Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Miss Patty Labelle who I think has been with us almost every year that we've been doing this.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, we love visiting her house. And every year, she has more and more people in her house.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I know.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: She has an incredible gathering of family.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: She throws great party.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes. COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I would love that.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: On the riser coming up, we've got Amy Sedaris, Bridget Everett, Matt Rogers and Bowen Yang. We've got a lot of fun.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It's a lot of fun.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I'm very excited about tonight.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes. It's a night of traditions, of course. And, yes, we're excited. We're excited. Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Speaking of traditions.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It is -- It's just -- it's the top of the hour.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Right, 8

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes. And so we've been here for seven years doing this.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And for most of those years --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Are you asking about alcohol?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, at the top of the hour, we typically have a toast. And I feel that I'm hearing from a lot of people. And I guess I'm just wondering, does daddy get his juice? Like --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Can daddy get his juice responsibly?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Of course. Always.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, look, to be honest, I do not -- I do not have it. I do not bring anything.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You didn't bring anything?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: No, I did not. No.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, Anderson, this is why I'm a really good partner to you. I got it.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK? We're doing this.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: How did this tradition begin again?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Just I came into a show and it was like we got to do shots. OK. So here we go.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: So what is -- so what are the rules here?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: The rules are that we are going to do a toast at the top of every hour.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You at home are hanging out with us. And we want to toast with you at the top of every hour with whatever you feel comfortable toasting with. Orange juice, whatever. This is a communal experience. All of us together.We realize we are just wallpaper on your television for the next five hours. And we're cool with that. But at the top, we want you to lean in and say, we've got to join these guys.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Sweetie (inaudible) jacket like that it's hard to be a wallpaper.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: All right. Wow. You had nice things to say about it earlier.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, no.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And now -- right here. Let me pour you up.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I don't drink.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And so I think now Colbert (PH) made us do a shot a couple of weeks ago. But I think that this may be kind of the first tequila you will have since --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: This is the first tequila --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- two years ago.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Two years ago. Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: That's -- that is true.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Anderson, love you so much.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: All right.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Thank you for having me.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Thank you. COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Cheers to everybody at home.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Here we go. It's good, right? OK. I feel loosen up already. You good?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yeah.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: So how were your holidays?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: It's a long night.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: You -- Andy and I, we both have kids. We both have two kids. So this for us, this holiday season was like --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Boy, you really can't get it together.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I really --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Is it worse than the pickle juice?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yeah.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yeah.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It's -- I don't understand why people do this.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, you're going to understand me a little bit, baby. By the way, we had a lovely play date today.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We did. We have good guests.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Your kids came over to my house.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And I should mention that all of our kids, I know at the top of the hour, are watching us right now. So will you all indulge me? Hey, Ben and Lucy.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Hey, Wyatt. Hey, Sebastian.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Hi.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: This is the first year that my son Wyatt, who's three and a half, going to be four in April, understood who Santa was, included -- and got excited about Santa. So it was such an exciting Christmas for that reason.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And Santa, we left him. And Wyatt wanted to leave him M&M's, a banana, and a protein bar and milk. And Santa ate all of it.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh, really? He ate the protein.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: He did. He ate the protein.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, Ben is telling anyone who will listen, that we are Jewish. And Santa does not come to our house.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Really?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: So.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: That's what -- really?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: There you go. Yes. He knows. He knows.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And did you tell him that? I mean, that we're Jewish?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: That Santa doesn't come?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: No. He kind of put the pieces together there. Yeah.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Interesting. Wow.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. You were in Paris over Christmas?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes. I went to Paris over Christmas, which my partner in parenthood, Ben, his family is French. And so my kids are speaking French. And so they all went, and we all went, and they were all speaking French, the kids. I don't know what they're talking about.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Right. So you haven't, in all these years, picked up any French?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I mean, I can say a little bit. But the thing that drives -- OK. I'm just going to -- the thing that drives me nuts about France is --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. Good. For our French viewers, listen up.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: They don't know what iced coffee is. So any place you go to get --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: They don't know what ice is, period. They do not care for ice.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: They don't care for ice. But literally, I would go into every cafe and ask for an iced coffee. And they would look at me as if I was the first person in the world who has ever even mentioned that there is such a thing as black coffee with ice.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Listen, I'm an ice queen. I order ice everywhere I go. And nobody wants to bring me ice. What kind of time? I brought some with me today and hope to --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Didn't Madonna recently just call you a queen?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: A troublemaking queen. Yes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: A troublemaking queen. Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: She did it from the stage at the Barclays Center.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Wow.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You know what, if the shoe fits, what can I say? You are a thoroughbred parent, though. This guy will be like, I'll say, oh, where are you going for the break? We both have time off at the same time. He'll say, oh, we're looking at Morocco, or you went to Colombia earlier.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yeah, I went to Colombia.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I'm taking my kids to Florida this week. And you would think we're going to Australia. I mean, you're a very brave parent.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I did have one of those -- I was the person on the plane with the child who was screaming in the middle of the night. We were in Brazil and flying back. And literally at one point, like this is our --It's a 10-hour flight, two hours into -- Sebastian who had been sleeping on me, because he's too little to have a seat of his own, wakes up. And for the next eight hours --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I want to sleep on you.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: What?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I want to sleep on you.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I don't even know what that means. For the last -- for the eight hours he was the guy -- the kid who was screaming. At one point in mid-scream, the flight attendant came up and said, do you think he'd like a fruit plate? I was like, I don't think he wants a fruit plate. No, I don't know what he wants, but I don't think it's a fruit plate.But they were very sweet. All the flight attendants were lovely on United. Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Did that shot make you cry a little bit? Maybe your eyes water. Oh, my God. Wow.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes. What happened -- you were at this thing the jingle ball, which I --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I was. I was introducing Cher-

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Right. You were -- COHENoh, this is what you're talking to me?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: This is what I'm talking about. So you got --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: -- criticized for what you were wearing --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I did. I got roast. I cannot believe you're showing that on CNN.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, sweetie, but can we just show the picture again? Because --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Okay. Well --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I don't know if we can do a split screen or something, because aren't you wearing the same shoes?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, no. Tearing the same shoes. There's nothing wrong with these shoes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, yes, if you're a kid. Sweetie, you're 55 years old.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Sweetie, no, no, no, no. Okay. All right.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: You're a father.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. I love my shirt. That's an Alex Mill shirt.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I heard a comedian --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I love it.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: A comedian say that you were trying to appeal to your step -- to relate to your steps on with that, which I think is kind of funny.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I feel like right tonight, I feel like I look like Logan Roy, and he looks like Kendall Roy. I feel like -- you know what? There's a slight feeling of you just like just --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Trying to --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Trying to --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- get you?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Trying to go for it.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, yes, yes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You feel a little like Logan.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: My son right now is obsessed with Band-Aids. I don't know for you who have kids. And I know a lot of kids are watching right now if you have their kids up. So I don't know if your kids are also obsessed with Band-Aids. I didn't realize Band-Aids and stickers were such a thing.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: That's why it's in his legs.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: So that's why it's his legs.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh, my God. That's --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Which I rarely show because I feel like --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Are those stickers or --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: No. There's a couple of stickers, but --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. Well that's --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: But there's like -- the most he's had like 14 Band-Aids on his legs at one time.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: That's fun.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Which I can't have him wear short pants because I feel like people will think, you know, I'm --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Right. Cutting your own child.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: -- I'm abusing him in some way. I'm a terrible parent.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Ben is in a moment right now where he thinks everyone with gray hair except me are my parents, Ma and Pa. His grandparents came in with a picture of Andy Warhol the other day and he goes, this is Ma. I'm like, that's Andy Warhol, dude. That's not Ma.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: That's so relatable.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And it's a guy.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: That's such a relatable story. Every kid does that with their Andy Warhol.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Listen, you do not want to start with me 10 minutes into the show about relatable, Vanderbilt boy.Oh, my God, we are off and running. This shot really -- you know what? You're a -- you're a -- what did she- you're a trouble-making queen.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Also, my son lost this year, lost his bear. COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, and Mark and Kelly's genius staff and live viewers tracked down. This was the bear that was lost. Just known as --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Adorable.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: -- bear.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And that's also bear and -- but it disappeared. Then, of course, live viewers found two of them on Etsy, one in Australia, one in London. I got them both on Etsy. So there's two replacements.But then we found it --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Why it take to the replacement?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: No. Not interested replacements.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, yes, yes. Of course.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: But then we found the original one because, of course, it was right under the car seat and on the front seat where, of course, it would have been. And I thought people would look, but nobody had.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Did you wash it?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And but now (INAUDIBLE) in Paris. It's gone.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh, my God. Relatable.Coming up, we have a performance by the Jonas Brothers. Plus, my dear friend, Amy Sedaris, swept through traffic --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Wow.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- and security to come right here and humor us.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Less than four hours to the Ball Drop, Times Square getting more packed.Joining us now, the queen of entertaining on the biggest night for entertaining Amy Sedaris. AMY SEDARIS, AMERICAN ACTRESS: Oh, gosh. Hi, you guys.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Wow. You look so amazing. Wow.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Oh. That's nice for you to say. Thank you.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Wow, you swept all the way in the --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: How was getting in?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I did. It wasn't so bad. They just kept changing the drop off avenues. I thought I had to walk from 10th, but I wore rain boots, so.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: You guys look good. I'm happy to be here.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Have you seen Andy's shoes, by the way?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I love Andy's shoes. They're so adorable.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. All right. OK. OK.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Amy, you know, we are -- well, do you want a shot?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: OK. You know, I am entertaining tonight. I have a party to get to.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: You're hosting --

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I'm hosting.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- a New Year's party now.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Yes, I am.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Wow.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: What should people expect at a party you hosted at your house?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I haven't had a -- I haven't had a -- I hosted a party in a really long time. I don't know what you asked me, but this is my question.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I haven't --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: What should people expect tonight? What's going to happen at your party tonight?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Well, it's about casting your party. It's about who you invite, really.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: You know what I mean? And say when it starts and when it ends. And then if it goes on longer, it goes on longer.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Do you put an ending time to your party?

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I heard someone say, well, I'm hosting it with two other people. They're going to put an ending time. But it's --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And what time would they end the New Year's Eve party?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. Do your shot.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: Oh, my God. It's so big.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: OK, that's good for me.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. Now, by the way, we're drinking tonight. So, is there --

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
utterances.sentences: I know you are.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Is there any --

utterances.speaker: SEDARIS
